phrases: No wonder you smell so bad.
You would better use treatment, too, and not just shampoo.
I cannot believe you put up with having such long hair.
Y-Yeah, well, I wash it every day.
I wonder if you could care for so much hair.
I would never let it get that long in the first place.
I just imagined you with long hair, and now I feel sick.
I just noticed I am talking with Nino.
I do not even care about my hairstyle.
Then do something about your weird hair.
This is the only cut Raiha knows how to do.
I guess I have no trouble talking to her when it is just one-to-one.
Why are you making your family cut your hair?
Why do not you get your family to do yours, too?
Maybe I do not fully understand Nino yet.
What happened before you came here?
That was the first time I saw you looking depressed.
I like being alone, but I get bored not having anyone to talk to.
Five years ago, I met a girl.
I am glad you seem to be well.
You are going to listen to me, or you are not getting this back.
How do I keep you from running away?
I do not know your name.
It is been five years, huh?
To meet you as you are now.
I heard you have been studying hard since then,
and that you are top of your class now.
And now you are a tutor, huh?
I do not know if you would believe me,
but I am teaching my classmates.
I thought you would be more surprised.
I never realized quintuplets actually exist!
I have only seen them in TV shows!
The problem is that they are all idiots.
The eldest is an idiot chasing after a dream.
She does not expect it to work out, but at least she has tenacity, I guess.
The second sister is a family-obsessed idiot.
She is really protective of her sisters, and she is quick to lash out.
And I thought that is all she was, but now, I do not really know.
The third is an idiot with self-esteem issues.
She was glum and listless when I first met her,
but she is been more vibrant lately.
The fourth is a meathead idiot.
but she is the biggest source of my headaches.
No, I might be imagining it.
The youngest is a stuck-up idiot.
I do not get along with her.
I do not want her abilities to go to waste.
But I guess I am surprised.
You are facing your problems head-on now, huh?
I think you are someone who is needed now.
Itsuki said the same thing to me.
You should never have come into our lives!
I have not changed at all since then.
I guess I should get out of your life, then, if I am tying you down.
You can have this back, as I promised.
But I am not giving this back.
Because I am never going to see you again.
Open that once you learn to accept yourself.
Sorry to bore you with my story.
Y-You have liked her for five years now, have not you?
I-It is not that I liked her.
I admired her and appreciated her.
That is what it means to like someone!
Anyway, you do not need to feel so bad for me.
Well, that was a perfect sob story!
I am sure there is at least one person on this planet
who would fall for an insensitive guy like you.
Why are you out of the bath?
We have seen each other naked already.
You have been working on these?
You picked out different problems for each of us, did not you?
Honestly, I do feel b-bad about what happened.
Go apologize to Itsuki now, too.
Are you still pissed off about her slapping you?
She is never done that before.
I feel like I do not know her anymore.
I have a hard time believing that.
You have got to stop being so stubborn, too.
Your hair's so shiny today, Onii-chan.
What happened while you were with Nino?
A-Anyway, I know you two go out for lunch together and stuff.
I am sure you can go back to being likeminded, close sisters once you cool off.
Nino and I are not exactly likeminded.
Even when we went to the movies the other day...
It got boring after Ichika died.
That one in the trailers looked really good, though.
Our tastes have drifted apart over the years.
I would not want to see either of those movies.
I have to prepare the garbage for tomorrow.
Tomorrow is non-combustible garbage day, right?
I will take it out in the morning.
Itsuki-san, where do rubber bands go again?
They go with the combustible garbage.
Man, it is great having you around, Itsuki-chan.
I am starting to understand why you were so annoyed
when I was over at your place.
I am going to call room service.
I will choose something for you.
Wait, why are you even here?!
What happened to how reserved you were yesterday?!
We have to deal with the problem at hand.
I was here for the finals.
I made it through the day's quota!
I wonder if Itsuki and Nino are studying right about now.
We know where they are, right?
I am sure they will be back soon.
Do you think they are finally contacting us?
Sorry, it was from the captain of the track team.
I was honestly shocked by what happened yesterday.
I do not know why Rena showed up now,
but there is something she taught me.
You cannot change the fact that people change.
You just have to forget the past and accept what comes.
So you should make up and go home, too.
and I am going to talk to myself.
Back when we used to look the same and have the same personality,
I felt like all of our thoughts were shared.
But that changed five years ago.
It was like they would left the quintuplet nest and me behind with it.
I am the only one who has not been able to move on.
I cannot even change the length of my hair.
That is why I have to force myself to leave the nest.
Before I am left all alone.
So this is what I would failed to grasp.
This mindset of hers, a result of how much she cares for her sisters.
Is that really what you want?
I have to forget the past and move on.
Other than that, if there is anything I regret,
Maybe it is because I never got to say goodbye.
I thought I could find some closure if I could see him again,
but he will not let me forget him.
What would you do if I said you could meet him?
Come in and make yourself at home.
What do I have to do for Nino today?
A: Pretend to be make-believe man Kintaro,
and play along until she gets over him.
B: Reveal everything and ask her to forgive me.
The first option is the correct one if I am thinking about the future, but...
do not you have something to say to me?
It might not be that simple.
There is something I have to tell you.
I will forgive you for standing me up on campfire night.
Although, that was just me aggressively telling you to come anyway.
Okay, that is the end of that.
You promised to hang out with me all day today, right?
You better not bail on me this time.
I do not think now's the time to tell her who I am.
Let us get this done quick.
Sorry, I have to make a phone call.
And I get so nervous, I cannot even look him in the eye.
Kintaro-kun does not hate cream puffs, does he?
I was thinking of making cream puffs.
I never thought you would mess up cooking, Nino.
Oh, Futaro told me you are good at cooking.
Hey, he just called me by my first name!
Quit calling me over stupid crap!
Let us call your sisters over to help finish them.
I do not want them to get in the way.
I only want you here with me.
Uesugi said the same thing, too.
I get that I am causing him a lot of trouble, messing up his tutoring and stuff...
All he ever talks about is studying.
I do not care about the exams!
I just want the five of you to be together!
I have something important to tell you.
I have a feeling this is going to be long.
Can I go to the washroom?
I guess you could say that.
Come to the cafe on the first floor.
Why are you drenched in sweat?
I think he might ask me out.
I mean, he looked all serious, and he said he has something important to tell me.
I appreciate you letting me see him.
I am going to find a conclusion to my current relationship with him.
I told you, you would better not break your promise.
I am obviously going to see through your disguise.
You are not twins, after all.
The customer here just checked out.
Meet onhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhh the track at 6hhhhhhhh tomorrow morning!
I heard she is taking the day off.
Let us go see Nino directly.
Sadly, that will not work anymore, either.
That is all I can do right now.
You have been weird all day today.
We have to go find the other problem child.
It is all thanks to you that we made it into the marathon.
We are all counting on the gifted runner, Nakano-san.
The end times must be nigh.
You are quite impressive, practicing for a meet when we have finals coming up.
We do not have time to care about exams.
Yotsuba, you are not pushing yourself too hard, are you?
Well, if you say so, I will not stop you.
I will not be interrupting, then, will I?
Which palace did Louis XIV of France build?
Who is the author of Run, Melos!?
What is the fourth element on the periodic table?
But she is learned more than I expected.
Is she actually going to do both?
You should go take a break.
We are going to a training camp this weekend.
I do not know about that.
I thought we were taking the weekend off.
We are not going to two-peat the meet with that kind of thinking.
You are going to give me a heart attack.
I have to brush my teeth, too.
You were holding onto your toothbrush without actually brushing again.
I will do it for you.
I used to do this for you all the time.
I am not a kid anymore, though.
This is what grown-up toothpaste tastes like.
I guess you are still too young for it.
You may have grown big, but you have not changed.
You are always going to be my little sister, no matter how much you grow up.
I wish you would depend on me more.
Would it be bad if I said I wanted to quit the team?
You can quit if you want.
I would be causing trouble for the team.
Look what you made me say, playing the big sister all of a sudden.
You are still a little girl as long as you are wearing underwear like this.
And keep them away when Uesugi-san's around!
Yes, she wears little girl panties.
I am going to see the track team tomorrow.
We are going to free Yotsuba.
Am I ever going to get any privacy?
